# Energy Predictor Dashboard

## Overview

This project is an operational dashboard for predicting energy usage in different stations. The dashboard provides an overview of the energy usage in real-time and historical data. It also includes features such as data visualization, alert system, and data download.

## Features

- Real-time energy usage data
- Historical data visualization
- User-friendly interface

Requirements

- Python 3.8+
- Streamlit 0.85+
- Pandas 1.2+
- NumPy 1.20+
- Matplotlib 3.4+
- Seaborn 0.11+
- Installation

Clone the repository: git clone https://github.com/nlishivha-1/energy


Install the required libraries: pip install -r requirements.txt
Run the dashboard: streamlit run app.py
Usage

Open the dashboard in your web browser: http://localhost:8501
Select a station from the dropdown menu
View real-time energy usage data
View historical data visualization
Download data as a CSV file
Contributing

Contributions are welcome! If you have any ideas or suggestions for improving the dashboard, please open an issue or submit a pull request.

